<DocsLayout title="Getting Started">
  <h2>Installation</h2>
  <p>Requires Python 3.10+.</p>
  <pre><code>pip install declarativedocs</code></pre>

  <h2>CLI Usage</h2>
  <p>The <code>ddf</code> command compiles a YAML file to its target format:</p>
  <pre><code>ddf presentation.yaml</code></pre>
  <p>This produces <code>presentation.pptx</code> in the same directory. You can also specify an output path:</p>
  <pre><code>ddf presentation.yaml -o output/deck.pptx</code></pre>

  <h2>Python API</h2>
  <pre><code class="language-python">from declarativedocs import compile

# Auto-detects format from YAML content
output_path = compile("presentation.yaml")

# Or specify output path explicitly
output_path = compile("presentation.yaml", "output/deck.pptx")</code></pre>

  <h2>Your First Presentation</h2>
  <p>Create a file called <code>hello.yaml</code>:</p>
  <pre><code class="language-yaml">presentation:
  layout: "16x9"
  title: "Hello DDF"

  theme:
    colors:
      primary: "1E2761"
      white: "FFFFFF"

  slides:
    - background: $primary
      elements:
        - type: text
          x: 1
          y: 2
          w: 8
          h: 2
          text: "Hello, World!"
          size: 48
          color: $white
          bold: true
          align: center</code></pre>

  <p>Then compile it:</p>
  <pre><code>ddf hello.yaml
# ✓ hello.pptx</code></pre>
</DocsLayout>
